---
strictness: high
focus_areas: ["error-handling", "types", "modularity", "claims-discipline"]
use_clean_slate: true
repo_gates:
  - "./build.sh check"
  - "zig build check-parity"
notes: >
  Copy to the host project as .claude/modern-refactor.local.md (or equivalent).
  Not loaded from inside modern-refactor/ automatically — host-side optional settings.
---

# modern-refactor local settings (example)

- Prefer parallel extracts before cutover on contract-heavy code.
- Never invent CLI/MCP surfaces; defer to `src/cli/usage.zig` and MCP handlers.
- After docs edits, keep claims aligned with `docs/contracts/external-claims-audit.mdx`.
